main event: Three unidentified flying objects were sighted in the sky over Belmar, New York on December 1, 1953.
interesting points: The objects were described as bright, round, and silver or white in color.
The objects moved very rapidly in a southeasterly direction, much faster than any jet aircraft the witness had seen.
The objects appeared to be at a very high altitude.
The sighting was reported to the nearest Air Force office.
The document was part of the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book investigation into unidentified flying objects.
result: insufficient data to make a determination
sighted object: three bright, round, silver or white objects
